Germany Approves Algeria Defense Contracts, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   P a t r i c k   D o n a h u e
-- 
2011-07-04T07:43:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/germany-approves-algeria-defense-contracts-handelsblatt-says.html
The German government has approved
billions of euros-worth of defense transactions with  Algeria  and
Saudia Arabia,  Handelsblatt  reported, citing government
officials.  Contracts in Algeria worth about 10 billion euros ($14.6
billion) were approved for companies including  MAN SE (MAN) ,
 Rheinmetall AG (RHM) ,  Daimler AG (DAI) ,  ThyssenKrupp AG (TKA)  and European
Aeronautic, Defence & Space Co., Handelsblatt said. They include
projects such as building military vehicles, naval vessels and
border security, according to the newspaper.  Germany ’s Federal Security Council gave preliminary
approval for the delivery of more than 200 Leopard tanks from
Rheinmetall and Krauss-Maffei Wegmann GmbH,  Der Spiegel  magazine
said in this week’s edition.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patrick Donahue in Berlin at  at
 pdonahue1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  